cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper analyzes text corpora from various sources to understand public and media opinion on robots. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper examines public opinion on robots through social media platforms like Twitter and Kickstarter. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The study investigates the societal impact of robots and their acceptance by the public. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper may touch upon software engineering aspects of robotics, such as the development of natural language processing algorithms for analyzing text corpora. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper may discuss the interaction between humans and robots, as well as the design of robots for social and assistive purposes.
